This paper discusses trajectory outcomes in mechanical systems subject to unilateral constraints, which is a common topic in robotics. The mention of locomotion and manipulation suggests that the paper may fall under the robotics subfield (cs.RO). The use of intermittent contact also suggests that the paper may be related to control systems (cs.SY) and mechanical engineering (cs.ME). Additionally, the paper may involve machine learning (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for analyzing the trajectory outcomes.
